from\": 1272, \"to\": 1281}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's 9,900 miles between Paris and Tahiti, which makes this the biggest distance between a host city and an Olympic venue, beating Stockholm - which staged equestrian in 1958 when Melbourne hosted everything else - by 100 miles.\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1309, \"end\": 1314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.722383941865614e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999994229256, \"rank\": 5.771289083583053e-10, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 1415, \"end\": 1424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm\", \"score\": 0.9999999638566812, \"rank\": 3.6127344347640665e-08, \"text\": \"Stockholm\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm\"}, {\"begin\": 1464, \"end\": 1473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.9997056404798348, \"rank\": 0.00027132450809293527, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"9,900 miles\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1300}, {\"ngram\": \"a host city\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1384}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic venue\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1405}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1491}, {\"ngram\": \"100 miles\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But from a sporting point of view, it's perfectly logical.\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 157